00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:25,916
to do with Endymion?

252
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,583
[ARISA] Yeah. How did you
guess? They chose my song

253
00:12:28,666 --> 00:12:31,000
to be the theme for
the Endymion campaign.

254
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,541
[INDEX]
Hey, I know what that is!

255
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:34,583
It's an elevator
that goes into space.

256
00:12:34,666 --> 00:12:36,500
Arisa, are you
going into space, too?

257
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:38,625
[ARISA] I'm still not
sure about that, actually.

258
00:12:38,708 --> 00:12:39,958
It does sound like
there's going to be

259
00:12:40,041 --> 00:12:41,333
an opening ceremony, though.

260
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:43,083
[INDEX giggles]

261
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:46,083
--[INDEX] Excuse me! I'll take
--[KAMIJO] Enough!

262
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:48,875
--an order of fried oysters--
--Take pity on me!

263
00:12:48,958 --> 00:12:51,000
[INDEX exhales heavily]

264
00:12:51,083 --> 00:12:52,833
Your wish is really
coming true, huh?

265
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,458
You must be so happy.

266
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:55,916
Mhmmm.

267
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,750
It may sound strange,
but I've always had

268
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:03,041
good luck like that.
I know this only happened...

269
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:05,208
because I'm a
really lucky girl.

270
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:09,291
C'mon give
yourself some credit.

271
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:10,666
Huh?

272
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:12,750
Success isn't about luck.

273
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:14,708
You have to be willing
to get out there.

274
00:13:14,791 --> 00:13:16,625
To stand in the batter's box.

275
00:13:16,708 --> 00:13:17,875
[KAMIJO] To swing
for all you're worth,

276
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:19,833
hoping you'll
get a good hit!

277
00:13:20,791 --> 00:13:22,250
[KAMIJO] Or not.

278
00:13:24,875 --> 00:13:27,291
I hate to tell you, but
that wasn't very convincing.

279
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:29,041
Is there more?

280
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:31,416
'Kay, fine. Luck as bad as mine

281
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,125
does sometimes come into play.

282
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:34,500
[KAMIJO] But that's
not true for you.

283
00:13:34,583 --> 00:13:36,208
You were chosen for your talent.

284
00:13:36,291 --> 00:13:37,625
And personally,
I think that's something

285
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:39,541
you can be really proud of.

286
00:13:39,625 --> 00:13:41,375
You're so sweet.

287
00:13:41,458 --> 00:13:43,750
Uh! Hey! Look out!

288
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:00,583
[ARISA sighs]

289
00:14:00,666 --> 00:14:03,625
I can't remember the
last time I had so much fun!

290
00:14:03,708 --> 00:14:05,666
Thanks a lot. It was really
nice hanging out with

291
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:08,208
the two of you
for the entire day.

292
00:14:08,291 --> 00:14:11,250
[panting]

293
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:15,041
Hey, you know. I'm
actually a Level 0, too.

294
00:14:15,125 --> 00:14:17,291
[KAMIJO] So I guess that
makes it extra inspiring to me

295
00:14:17,375 --> 00:14:19,333
when somebody's
dream comes true.

296
00:14:19,416 --> 00:14:20,750
You're making me blush!

297
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:23,000
He's not alone, though.
I love seeing someone

298
00:14:23,083 --> 00:14:24,583
work so hard
for their future.

299
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:26,125
It really motivates me.

300
00:14:26,208 --> 00:14:27,958
Yeah, I know!
Doesn't it make you

301
00:14:28,041 --> 00:14:29,375
wanna shoot for the stars?

302
00:14:29,458 --> 00:14:32,458
[INDEX] Yes! Wait!
That doesn't sound right!

303
00:14:32,541 --> 00:14:35,166
I already have a noble
calling, thank you very much.

304
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,500
I'm a Sister!

305
00:14:36,583 --> 00:14:38,666
Should I take your casual
dismissal of that fact

306
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:41,041
as an insult to the
entire English Church?

307
00:14:41,125 --> 00:14:42,916
[KAMIJO] Calm down! That's
not what I meant at all!

308
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,000
I was talking about
something more personal.

309
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:47,250
Like helping out with
the housework, for example.

310
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:48,750
[INDEX] Shut up!
I eat, you clean.

311
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:49,875
That's how it works.

312
00:14:49,958 --> 00:14:51,333
[KAMIJO] Well, it
doesn't work for me!

313
00:14:51,416 --> 00:14:53,791
I mean, how can you
be a nun and a glutton?

314
00:14:53,875 --> 00:14:54,791
Listen.

315
00:14:54,875 --> 00:15:06,416
[ARISA singing a melody]

316
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:16,458
[singing continues]

317
00:15:34,208 --> 00:15:36,083
That was a beautiful
melody, Arisa.

318
00:15:36,166 --> 00:15:37,333
I really enjoyed it.

319
00:15:37,416 --> 00:15:38,708
Hey, I've heard that.

320
00:15:38,791 --> 00:15:40,833
In fact, it's one of the
songs I downloaded earlier.

321
00:15:40,916 --> 00:15:41,833
[ARISA giggles]

322
00:15:41,916 --> 00:15:44,041
[KAMIJO]
Does it have any lyrics?

323
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:46,291
[ARISA] No, not yet.
I'm still working on them.

324
00:15:46,375 --> 00:15:48,791
Thank you again.
I had a wonderful time.

325
00:15:48,875 --> 00:15:50,416
I can let you guys
know when my concert

326
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:52,375
is going to be,
if you'd like to come.

327
00:15:52,458 --> 00:15:53,333
Sounds good.

328
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:55,500
We can't wait to
see you perform.

329
00:15:55,583 --> 00:16:03,041
♪

330
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:06,375
I call on Undine by
the symbol of the chalice.

331
00:16:06,458 --> 00:16:08,958
That which is distilled
from all things.

332
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:11,458
Uh...!

333
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:14,708
[ALL gasp]

334
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:17,000
[ARISA] Whoa! What's that?

335
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:20,541
[BOTH] Uh!

336
00:16:22,541 --> 00:16:23,708
What's happening?

337
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:24,916
[INDEX] Be careful, Toma!

338
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,375
[gasps]

339
00:16:26,458 --> 00:16:28,875
[INDEX] It's a spell that
calls upon a water element.

340
00:16:28,958 --> 00:16:38,916
♪

341
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:42,875
And that means these are
magicians we're up against.

342
00:16:42,958 --> 00:16:44,333
[ALL] Ah!

343
00:16:49,458 --> 00:16:52,083
I want both of you
to stay back, okay?

344
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:54,833
You're up Marybeth!
Slow him down for me!

345
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,208
Ugh! The ground!

346
00:16:59,291 --> 00:17:00,541
Jane! Now!

347
00:17:00,625 --> 00:17:09,000
♪

348
00:17:09,083 --> 00:17:10,458
[JANE gasps]

349
00:17:14,875 --> 00:17:18,541
[KAMIJO] What do you want
with us? Who are you people?

350
00:17:21,416 --> 00:17:23,708
[screams]

351
00:17:23,791 --> 00:17:27,250
What happened? Was
that Spell Intercept?

352
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:28,708
Yaaa!

353
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:35,250
Uh--!

354
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:40,083
Wait, is that--?

355
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:43,625
[MARYBETH coughing]

356
00:17:43,708 --> 00:17:45,583
Thanks, Master.

357
00:17:45,666 --> 00:17:47,208
Why did you
act on your own?

358
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:49,875
I told you to wait
for my order, didn't I?

359
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:51,375
Mmm.

360
00:17:51,458 --> 00:17:53,666
[running footsteps]

361
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:56,750
[KAMIJO] It is you!
What the hell, Stiyl?

362
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:58,791
What are you doing here?

363
00:18:00,583 --> 00:18:03,458
Move it, kid. Fortis 931!

364
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:04,958
Your magic name?

365
00:18:08,916 --> 00:18:10,375
Are you serious?

366
00:18:10,458 --> 00:18:20,458
♪

367
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:26,666
What are you
three waiting for?

368
00:18:26,750 --> 00:18:28,708
[STIYL] Seize the girl!

369
00:18:28,791 --> 00:18:30,166
[KAMIJO] Arisa!

370
00:18:34,208 --> 00:18:35,625
Ah!

371
00:18:37,958 --> 00:18:39,250
Your right hand's powerful.

372
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:40,708
[STIYL] But it
can't destroy matter.

373
00:18:40,791 --> 00:18:42,875
Look out, Toma!

374
00:18:42,958 --> 00:18:44,583
[ARISA] Stop this!

375
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:47,666
No!

376
00:18:51,708 --> 00:18:53,250
What just happened?

377
00:18:56,166 --> 00:18:57,625
[gasps]

378
00:19:03,958 --> 00:19:05,375
What the hell?

379
00:19:05,458 --> 00:19:13,500
♪

380
00:19:13,583 --> 00:19:16,541
[beeping]

381
00:19:17,541 --> 00:19:27,500
♪

382
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:50,750
[beeping]

383
00:19:55,208 --> 00:19:56,583
Go!

384
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,000
[INDEX and KAMIJO] Ahh!

385
00:20:01,083 --> 00:20:09,625
♪

386
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:11,083
[STIYL grunts]

387
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:20,208
[KAMIJO grunts]

388
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:25,208
What is that thing?

389
00:20:25,291 --> 00:20:27,625
[WOMAN] Attention! We are
the Civil Conflict Resolution

390
00:20:27,708 --> 00:20:29,833
and Relief Patrol.
We're authorized by

391
00:20:29,916 --> 00:20:31,250
the city's governing board.

392
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:34,666
Be advised. This is
a special intervention.

393
00:20:37,416 --> 00:20:42,500
♪

394
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:43,916
[GIRL grunts]

395
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:55,375
♪

396
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:56,833
[STIYL] Ugh...

397
00:21:02,416 --> 00:21:04,416
Tch. Uh...

398
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:13,916
♪

399
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,375
[STIYL grunts]

400
00:21:17,916 --> 00:21:28,958
♪

401
00:21:29,041 --> 00:21:31,375
Come on, Styil. We're going
to have to get a handle

402
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:34,250
on this situation quickly,
or there'll be trouble.

403
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:35,625
Tch.

404
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:38,041
Well, ladies. You heard
what she said. Move out now.

405
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:39,500
[ALL] Right!

406
00:21:40,875 --> 00:21:50,333
♪

407
00:21:50,416 --> 00:21:52,166
[KANZAKI] What else can you do?

408
00:21:53,458 --> 00:22:03,416
♪

409
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:07,208
[KAMIJO] Hey, hold on!

410
00:22:07,291 --> 00:22:09,166
Why are you after Arisa?

411
00:22:09,250 --> 00:22:12,166
[GIRLS panting]

412
00:22:13,541 --> 00:22:15,333
[STIYL] She's more
important than you know.

413
00:22:15,416 --> 00:22:16,958
The girl could start a war,

414
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:20,291
between the scientific
and magic communities.

415
00:22:20,375 --> 00:22:22,250
What? A war?

416
00:22:24,958 --> 00:22:27,875
Hey! Care to elaborate?

417
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,375
Auhhh...

418
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:52,375
What do you want?
Who are you?

419
00:22:52,458 --> 00:22:54,166
As I was trying to
explain to you before,

420
00:22:54,250 --> 00:22:56,083
we are a specialized
task force charged with

421
00:22:56,166 --> 00:22:57,916
[WOMAN] maintaining
order in Academy City.

422
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,750
[KAMIJO] That doesn't
tell me what I need to know.

423
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:01,250
Are you trying to hurt
that girl over there

424
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:02,791
or are you on her side?

425
00:23:02,875 --> 00:23:04,375
[WOMAN] The combat we
just went through was part of

426
00:23:04,458 --> 00:23:06,875
our commissioned duty as
Civil Relief Patrol members.

427
00:23:06,958 --> 00:23:08,416
[KAMIJO] That doesn't
answer my question!

428
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:11,416
Hm. I'm warning you now.

429
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:13,083
Do not become
involved with her.

430
00:23:13,166 --> 00:23:15,458
Because if you do,
then chances are...

431
00:23:15,541 --> 00:23:17,166
[WOMAN] you will die.

432
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:18,708
[grunts]

433
00:23:20,208 --> 00:23:30,166
♪ [ARISA'S melody] ♪

434
00:23:40,208 --> 00:23:43,083
[gasps]

435
00:23:43,166 --> 00:23:44,541
[INDEX] Hm?

436
00:23:44,625 --> 00:23:46,750
Have a bad dream?

437
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:48,666
Oh, are you awake now?

438
00:23:50,708 --> 00:23:52,000
Um. Where am I?

439
00:23:52,083 --> 00:23:54,500
[INDEX] We brought you home.
Welcome to Toma's place.

440
00:23:54,583 --> 00:23:57,583
[KAMIJO] This isn't my home!
Uh, what I mean is,

441
00:23:57,666 --> 00:24:00,666
this is just a dorm
the school provides.

442
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:02,458
Oh, okay.

443
00:24:02,541 --> 00:24:05,541
Did you recognize any of
those people we saw earlier?

444
00:24:05,625 --> 00:24:07,708
[KAMIJO] Maybe you've
bumped in to them before?

445
00:24:07,791 --> 00:24:09,416
Mm-mmm.

446
00:24:09,500 --> 00:24:10,958
Mhmmm!

447
00:24:11,041 --> 00:24:13,000
It makes sense that she
wouldn't recognize them.

448
00:24:13,083 --> 00:24:14,541
After all, they were magi--

449
00:24:14,625 --> 00:24:18,250
Yeah, they were, majorly,
um, majorly powerful

450
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:21,291
in some way that can't possibly
be explained by science alone.

451
00:24:22,750 --> 00:24:24,500
Wait, do you believe
in it, too, Toma?

452
00:24:24,583 --> 00:24:27,208
I, um, believe in what?

453
00:24:27,291 --> 00:24:29,166
[INDEX grumbling]

454
00:24:29,250 --> 00:24:31,000
Well, it's like--you know...

455
00:24:31,083 --> 00:24:33,166
Like a strange,
mysterious sort of power

456
00:24:33,250 --> 00:24:35,000
that can't be
understood by science.

457
00:24:35,083 --> 00:24:36,541
I don't know about you,
but I've always found

458
00:24:36,625 --> 00:24:39,500
esper abilities to
be pretty mysterious.

459
00:24:39,583 --> 00:24:41,666
[breathing heavily]

460
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:42,833
[growls]

461
00:24:42,916 --> 00:24:45,791
Oh, uh. I'm sorry.
Don't kill me.

462
00:24:45,875 --> 00:24:47,541
Anyway. Arisa, are you
saying that you wish

463
00:24:47,625 --> 00:24:50,166
there was such a power?

464
00:24:50,250 --> 00:24:53,500
[ARISA] Well, actually.
I'm saying I have that power.

465
00:24:53,583 --> 00:24:55,083
[INDEX and KAMIJO] Huh?

466
00:24:56,375 --> 00:24:57,583
[ARISA] It happens
when I'm singing.

467
00:24:57,666 --> 00:25:00,541
It sounds crazy, but
it's true. I swear it is.

468
00:25:00,625 --> 00:25:03,708
When I sing, it's like I have
some unquantifiable power.

469
00:25:03,791 --> 00:25:06,458
They examine me regularly
at Kirigaoka Academy,

470
00:25:06,541 --> 00:25:09,500
where I go to
school, but no luck.

471
00:25:09,583 --> 00:25:12,375
Even they don't seem to
have any idea what it is.

472
00:25:12,458 --> 00:25:14,625
I can't help but wonder if
this power is the only reason

473
00:25:14,708 --> 00:25:16,583
that people listen to my songs.

474
00:25:16,666 --> 00:25:19,333
As much as I hate to think so,
it's totally possible.

475
00:25:19,416 --> 00:25:20,750
[KAMIJO] No way!

476
00:25:20,833 --> 00:25:23,791
If that were the case,
then my right hand would--

477
00:25:23,875 --> 00:25:24,750
--[KAMIJO] I, uh.
--[INDEX] Listen to him.

478
00:25:24,833 --> 00:25:25,750
He's right for once.

479
00:25:25,833 --> 00:25:27,500
Your songs are the real deal.

480
00:25:27,583 --> 00:25:28,958
[SPHINX meows]

481
00:25:30,416 --> 00:25:32,250
[meows]

482
00:25:34,041 --> 00:25:36,083
Thank you.

483
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:48,208
[ARISA] It may sound silly,
but I wanted to make

484
00:25:48,291 --> 00:25:51,625
everyone happy with my songs.
I knew that if I was making

485
00:25:51,708 --> 00:25:56,000
other people happy,
then I would be happy, too.

486
00:25:56,083 --> 00:25:58,166
[ARISA] But now,
if anyone were to get hurt

487
00:25:58,250 --> 00:26:00,541
because of my songs, then...

488
00:26:00,625 --> 00:26:03,166
Don't say that. You can't
think about backing out now.

489
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:05,666
Not after they've
accepted your audition.

490
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:07,250
What I'm trying
to say is,

491
00:26:07,333 --> 00:26:10,541
ultimately, singing is just
a selfish desire of mine.

492
00:26:10,625 --> 00:26:14,000
What if people come after
me like they did before?

493
00:26:14,083 --> 00:26:15,666
It could be worse this time.

494
00:26:15,750 --> 00:26:18,541
They could hurt
somebody close to me.

495
00:26:18,625 --> 00:26:20,458
So that's it?
You're giving up.

496
00:26:20,541 --> 00:26:22,291
You're going to
sacrifice your dream because

497
00:26:22,375 --> 00:26:25,041
somebody came along and
intimidated you with force?

498
00:26:25,125 --> 00:26:26,291
Mmm.

499
00:26:26,375 --> 00:26:29,541
Honestly. What do you
want more than anything?

500
00:26:30,416 --> 00:26:32,333
[ARISA] I want to sing.

501
00:26:32,416 --> 00:26:34,166
It's all I have.
It's what I love,

502
00:26:34,250 --> 00:26:36,000
what I'm passionate about.

503
00:26:37,250 --> 00:26:39,208
[meows]

504
00:26:42,541 --> 00:26:44,416
[KAMIJO] Then go ahead and sing.

505
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:46,041
Singing is what you love to do,

506
00:26:46,125 --> 00:26:47,666
and you really
have a gift for it.

507
00:26:47,750 --> 00:26:50,250
You can't give it up.

508
00:26:50,333 --> 00:26:52,208
We'll just have to
come up with a plan.

509
00:26:52,291 --> 00:26:54,666
