the spectators.

789
00:39:28,791 --> 00:39:30,541
And what about the
rest of your people?

790
00:39:30,625 --> 00:39:32,291
They're all right, too.

791
00:39:32,375 --> 00:39:33,625
The Black Crow Force
got through this

792
00:39:33,708 --> 00:39:35,458
without any injury.

793
00:39:35,541 --> 00:39:38,458
Wow, that really is
miraculous, isn't it?

794
00:39:38,541 --> 00:39:39,791
[groans]

795
00:39:39,875 --> 00:39:41,416
Do not speak that
word in my presence.

796
00:39:41,500 --> 00:39:44,291
Do you understand me?

797
00:39:44,375 --> 00:39:46,208
[SHUTAURA] Things just
happened to work out well.

798
00:39:46,291 --> 00:39:48,125
There's nothing
more to it than that.

799
00:39:48,208 --> 00:39:49,583
Nothing more
special than a random

800
00:39:49,666 --> 00:39:51,750
quantum mechanical deviation.

801
00:39:51,833 --> 00:39:53,541
That and people's
irrational need

802
00:39:53,625 --> 00:39:56,166
to sensationalize
a happy ending.

803
00:39:56,250 --> 00:39:58,541
[coughing]

804
00:39:58,625 --> 00:40:00,958
Humans have grown
indolent and foolish.

805
00:40:01,041 --> 00:40:03,000
Always waiting for
some great "unseen hand"

806
00:40:03,083 --> 00:40:04,708
to swoop in and save them.

807
00:40:04,791 --> 00:40:06,416
I get it. You lead
men into combat.

808
00:40:06,500 --> 00:40:09,000
That means you have to
maintain a tough exterior,

809
00:40:09,083 --> 00:40:11,416
but Arisa, she is
the real thing.

810
00:40:11,500 --> 00:40:13,375
Have you listened
to her songs before?

811
00:40:13,458 --> 00:40:15,541
You should really
give them a try sometime.

812
00:40:15,625 --> 00:40:19,833
They might even make someone
like you believe in miracles.

813
00:40:19,916 --> 00:40:22,166
[SHUTAURA] I was in an
accident. Because of that,

814
00:40:22,250 --> 00:40:25,083
my brain has lost the
ability to recognize music.

815
00:40:25,166 --> 00:40:26,583
[gasps]

816
00:40:26,666 --> 00:40:28,125
[SHUTAURA] I can
hear spoken words fine,

817
00:40:28,208 --> 00:40:31,500
but my brain can't process
rhythm and changes in pitch.

818
00:40:31,583 --> 00:40:33,125
Which means no music.

819
00:40:33,208 --> 00:40:34,875
Where I'm concerned,
a song is nothing but

820
00:40:34,958 --> 00:40:37,250
noise assaulting my ears.

821
00:40:37,333 --> 00:40:38,708
[sighs]

822
00:40:41,250 --> 00:40:43,041
[KAMIJO] I'm sorry.
What was your na--

823
00:40:43,125 --> 00:40:47,791
[SHUTAURA] I'm Shutaura.
Shutaura Sequenzia.

824
00:40:47,875 --> 00:40:50,291
[KAMIJO] I'm sorry,
Shutaura, really.

825
00:40:50,375 --> 00:40:52,791
[SHUTAURA] Why apologize?
I'm perfectly content

826
00:40:52,875 --> 00:40:54,833
with the way things are.

827
00:40:54,916 --> 00:40:56,625
[SHUTAURA] I'm never
swayed by popular music,

828
00:40:56,708 --> 00:40:58,125
and I don't jump on bandwagons

829
00:40:58,208 --> 00:41:01,083
or get distracted by
so-called "miracles."

