actually been proven yet.

937
00:45:26,250 --> 00:45:29,250
[KANZAKI] Well, what about you?
What's your opinion on it?

938
00:45:29,333 --> 00:45:30,875
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
I'm not entirely sure.

939
00:45:30,958 --> 00:45:34,416
Defining saints is always
such an imprecise business.

940
00:45:34,500 --> 00:45:36,833
It might help the
process if I could

941
00:45:36,916 --> 00:45:38,791
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
give you a thorough exam.

942
00:45:38,875 --> 00:45:40,791
Every last inch of you.

943
00:45:40,875 --> 00:45:42,583
Absolutely not!
Stay away from me!

944
00:45:42,666 --> 00:45:45,958
Well, whether Arisa's a saint
or not, one thing is clear.

945
00:45:46,041 --> 00:45:47,541
There are people in the
city who want to analyze

946
00:45:47,625 --> 00:45:48,708
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
whatever gifts she has

947
00:45:48,791 --> 00:45:50,958
and find a way to exploit them.

948
00:45:51,041 --> 00:45:54,500
Particularly that lolita
in charge of Orbit Portal.

949
00:45:54,583 --> 00:45:55,416
[ARISA] Here.

950
00:45:55,500 --> 00:45:56,166
Hm?

951
00:45:56,250 --> 00:45:57,708
The lyrics
to that song.

952
00:45:57,791 --> 00:46:00,125
I promised we'd sing
them together, didn't I?

953
00:46:00,208 --> 00:46:01,458
[gasps in awe]

954
00:46:01,541 --> 00:46:04,541
I think this deserves
a toast, so here's to you!

955
00:46:04,625 --> 00:46:06,291
Here's to you!

956
00:46:06,375 --> 00:46:07,625
[BOTH] Cheers!

