00:48:44,541 --> 00:48:46,958
[distant explosion]

1006
00:48:47,041 --> 00:48:50,208
♪

1007
00:48:50,291 --> 00:48:51,666
[STIYL gasps]

1008
00:48:54,708 --> 00:48:57,916
♪

1009
00:48:58,000 --> 00:49:00,333
[car tires screech]

1010
00:49:05,125 --> 00:49:06,000
[MARYE] Whew.

1011
00:49:06,083 --> 00:49:07,041
[MALLYBATH] Ugh.

1012
00:49:07,125 --> 00:49:08,541
[JANE] Owie.

1013
00:49:14,208 --> 00:49:16,625
Stop this, Styil!

1014
00:49:16,708 --> 00:49:18,708
[KAMIJO] You're jumping
the gun here, and you know it!

1015
00:49:18,791 --> 00:49:20,291
There's still no proof
that she's a saint,

1016
00:49:20,375 --> 00:49:22,291
so why don't you
just leave her alone?

1017
00:49:22,375 --> 00:49:23,125
[sighs]

1018
00:49:23,208 --> 00:49:25,208
Thanks, Kanzaki.

1019
00:49:25,291 --> 00:49:28,333
[STIYL] I have recently been
given a new set of orders.

1020
00:49:28,416 --> 00:49:30,041
You know what that
thing over there is?

1021
00:49:30,125 --> 00:49:31,916
Yeah, of course.
It's a space elevator.

1022
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:33,333
[STIYL] Nope.

1023
00:49:33,416 --> 00:49:36,958
Consider the Sumerian
ziggurats, the Tower of Babel.

1024
00:49:37,041 --> 00:49:38,583
When structures are
built on a scale that

1025
00:49:38,666 --> 00:49:40,708
exceeds the very
bounds of rationality,

1026
00:49:40,791 --> 00:49:43,291
they take on magical
properties, as well.

1027
00:49:43,375 --> 00:49:44,500
And you know what happens when

1028
00:49:44,583 --> 00:49:46,916
some evil mastermind
gets a saint involved?

1029
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:48,541
[STIYL] The structure
in question can become

1030
00:49:48,625 --> 00:49:50,708
a large-scale
magical instrument.

1031
00:49:50,791 --> 00:49:53,000
[KAMIJO] Hold on a second!
Are you saying there's someone

1032
00:49:53,083 --> 00:49:55,750
in Academy City who's
trying to use magic?

1033
00:49:55,833 --> 00:49:57,291
Uh.

1034
00:49:57,375 --> 00:50:00,333
[LADYLEE] It's me. Antiskill
is on the move. Withdraw now.

1035
00:50:00,416 --> 00:50:01,791
[SHUTAURA] Roger.

1036
00:50:11,500 --> 00:50:13,250
[SHUTAURA gasps]

1037
00:50:13,333 --> 00:50:16,666
It can't be. That's impossible!

1038
00:50:16,750 --> 00:50:20,166
[LADYLEE] Oh, dear. Found out
about that, have we? Alright.

1039
00:50:20,250 --> 00:50:23,166
Bring the girl back here
at once. We'll have a chat.

1040
00:50:26,958 --> 00:50:28,125
[SHUTAURA] Stay back!

1041
00:50:28,208 --> 00:50:30,333
[KAMIJO] Shutaura!
You don't have to do this!

1042
00:50:30,416 --> 00:50:31,791
Please, let her go!

1043
00:50:31,875 --> 00:50:33,666
This isn't your business!

1044
00:50:33,750 --> 00:50:35,750
[SHUTAURA] So why
are you interfering?

1045
00:50:38,625 --> 00:50:40,083
That's not good.

1046
00:50:43,375 --> 00:50:45,416
Get out of here! Now!

1047
00:50:49,083 --> 00:50:50,666
[KAMIJO yells]

1048
00:51:00,208 --> 00:51:02,291
[keyboard clicking]

1049
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:07,958
[sighs]

1050
00:51:08,041 --> 00:51:12,208
[cell phone ringing]

1051
00:51:12,291 --> 00:51:14,083
[MIKOTO] Saten's calling?

1052
00:51:14,916 --> 00:51:19,750
[MIKOTO] Hello, Saten.
Yeah, what's up? Uh huh, yeah.

1053
00:51:19,833 --> 00:51:21,250
What's that? Arisa's missing?

1054
00:51:21,333 --> 00:51:23,708
Yeah. They don't know
where she might be.

1055
00:51:23,791 --> 00:51:26,000
They're pretty certain
she's been abducted.

1056
00:51:26,083 --> 00:51:29,333
[MIKOTO] Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm. Alright, got it.

1057
00:51:29,416 --> 00:51:30,958
I'm heading out now.

1058
00:51:31,041 --> 00:51:32,416
[beep]

1059
00:51:35,500 --> 00:51:36,875
[door opens]

1060
00:51:36,958 --> 00:51:38,708
[door closes]

1061
00:51:38,791 --> 00:51:41,666
[footsteps]

1062
00:51:54,000 --> 00:51:56,416
[SHUTAURA] Who is this girl?

1063
00:51:56,500 --> 00:51:58,708
And what in the world is
she doing with this bracelet?

1064
00:51:58,791 --> 00:52:00,250
[door opens]

1065
00:52:00,333 --> 00:52:01,458
[LADYLEE] It's as I assumed.

1066
00:52:01,541 --> 00:52:03,500
You two are drawn
to one another.

1067
00:52:04,208 --> 00:52:06,416
On the day that the
Orion crashed to the Earth

1068
00:52:06,500 --> 00:52:08,708
there were eighty-eight
passengers and crew aboard.

1069
00:52:08,791 --> 00:52:10,625
[LADYLEE] When they
counted after the accident

1070
00:52:10,708 --> 00:52:13,333
they confirmed that there
were eighty-eight survivors.

1071
00:52:13,416 --> 00:52:16,250
It was truly a miracle.
Everyone said so.

1072
00:52:16,333 --> 00:52:19,833
But the truth is, there
was a single fatality.

1073
00:52:19,916 --> 00:52:23,666
The pilot of the Orion.
Daedalus Sequenzia.

1074
00:52:25,000 --> 00:52:28,125
That's right.
Your father died that day.

1075
00:52:28,208 --> 00:52:31,625
But, by the time his demise
was officially confirmed,

1076
00:52:31,708 --> 00:52:33,291
it was already too late.

1077
00:52:33,375 --> 00:52:35,250
The world was caught
up in the miracle.

1078
00:52:35,333 --> 00:52:36,875
[LADYLEE] So it was never
revealed that there were

1079
00:52:36,958 --> 00:52:39,000
actually eighty-nine
people on the plane

1080
00:52:39,083 --> 00:52:40,875
when it came crashing down.

1081
00:52:40,958 --> 00:52:42,958
There were only eighty-eight
when the plane took off,

1082
00:52:43,041 --> 00:52:45,333
but one girl appeared
suddenly in transit.

1083
00:52:45,416 --> 00:52:47,875
She appeared, and then
she worked a miracle.

1084
00:52:47,958 --> 00:52:49,958
[LADYLEE] This is that girl.

1085
00:52:50,041 --> 00:52:53,208
[SHUTAURA] Must you persist in
calling the accident a miracle?

1086
00:52:53,291 --> 00:52:55,958
[LADYLEE] You know, the way
that "accident" was designed,

1087
00:52:56,041 --> 00:52:58,125
nobody should have survived.

1088
00:52:58,208 --> 00:52:59,875
[SHUTAURA gasps]
What're you saying?

1089
00:52:59,958 --> 00:53:02,750
I was so confident. I thought
for sure that it would work.

1090
00:53:02,833 --> 00:53:04,083
[LADYLEE] However,
except for your father,

1091
00:53:04,166 --> 00:53:06,208
every single person lived.

1092
00:53:06,291 --> 00:53:10,083
Fortunately, it did produce an
especially useful by-product.

1093
00:53:10,166 --> 00:53:12,541
So in that sense,
I suppose it was a success.

1094
00:53:12,625 --> 00:53:14,875
[SHUTAURA]
The crash, it was you.

1095
00:53:16,791 --> 00:53:18,791
[SHUTAURA] You did this!

1096
00:53:18,875 --> 00:53:21,708
[grunting]

1097
00:53:21,791 --> 00:53:23,166
Uh...!

1098
00:53:26,541 --> 00:53:32,083
[panting]

1099
00:53:39,375 --> 00:53:41,041
[SHUTAURA] Who are you, girl?

1100
00:53:41,125 --> 00:53:46,291
♪

1101
00:53:46,375 --> 00:53:48,375
[LADYLEE chuckles]

1102
00:53:53,833 --> 00:53:55,208
[gasps]

1103
00:53:58,208 --> 00:54:00,083
[SHUTAURA] You're that,
guy from before!

1104
00:54:02,416 --> 00:54:05,791
[SHUTAURA struggling]

1105
00:54:05,875 --> 00:54:09,291
[LADYLEE] Are you finished
with your tantrum?

1106
00:54:09,375 --> 00:54:11,416
By my last count,
that's the sixteenth time

1107
00:54:11,500 --> 00:54:12,708
I've been stabbed now.

1108
00:54:12,791 --> 00:54:14,333
You're a monster.

1109
00:54:14,416 --> 00:54:15,875
Well, you could call me that.

1110
00:54:15,958 --> 00:54:18,791
I'm not an ordinary human,
that much is certain.

1111
00:54:18,875 --> 00:54:21,250
[LADYLEE] But then again,
neither are the two of you.

1112
00:54:21,333 --> 00:54:24,041
Which is why I'm
going to let you live.

1113
00:54:24,125 --> 00:54:26,208
[LADYLEE] I know how
you love miracles.

1114
00:54:26,291 --> 00:54:28,541
Be patient and you'll
see yet another one.

1115
00:54:28,625 --> 00:54:30,708
Whoever you are and whatever
it is you're planning,

1116
00:54:30,791 --> 00:54:34,458
I swear that I will stop
you! I swear, you hear me?

1117
00:54:34,541 --> 00:54:37,833
Yes, I look forward
to it. Take her away.

1118
00:54:40,583 --> 00:54:44,125
Now then, girl.
That just leaves you and me.

1119
00:54:49,541 --> 00:54:51,875
[LADYLEE] Good morning.

1120
00:54:51,958 --> 00:54:54,291
There's a little
favor I need from you,

1121
00:54:54,375 --> 00:54:56,916
if it's not too much trouble.

1122
00:54:57,000 --> 00:54:58,375
[cheering]

1123
00:54:58,458 --> 00:54:59,583
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER A]
Those with ticket numbers

1124
00:54:59,666 --> 00:55:02,416
two-zero-three-three
through two-one-five-two

1125
00:55:02,500 --> 00:55:04,666
please embark on the
Number Seventeen linear track.

1126
00:55:04,750 --> 00:55:05,875
[FEMALE NEWSCASTER B]
The much-anticipated unveiling

1127
00:55:05,958 --> 00:55:07,791
ceremony is
scheduled for tomorrow.

1128
00:55:07,875 --> 00:55:09,666
Accordingly, excited
guests have been rolling

1129
00:55:09,750 --> 00:55:11,750
in non-stop all day.

1130
00:55:11,833 --> 00:55:13,791
I don't believe it.
Are you sure?

1131
00:55:13,875 --> 00:55:16,666
Yeah. There's no sign of her.
She never came back.

1132
00:55:16,750 --> 00:55:19,083
I did some looking around,
too, but I came up empty.

1133
00:55:19,166 --> 00:55:21,291
Where is she?

1134
00:55:21,375 --> 00:55:23,583
--[MIKOTO] Well...
--[INDEX] Toma.

1135
00:55:23,666 --> 00:55:25,000
Hmm.

1136
00:55:25,083 --> 00:55:26,125
Hmm.

1137
00:55:26,208 --> 00:55:29,041
Wha... Huh...?

1138
00:55:29,125 --> 00:55:31,708
My goodness.
Injured again, are you?

1139
00:55:31,791 --> 00:55:32,875
[FROG DOCTOR]
You're trying to set a new

1140
00:55:32,958 --> 00:55:34,875
hospital admittance
record, is that it?

1141
00:55:34,958 --> 00:55:37,583
Um, no, sir. Not exactly.

1142
00:55:37,666 --> 00:55:39,500
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
Kami! How's it goin'?

1143
00:55:39,583 --> 00:55:41,250
Can we borrow
you for a second?

1144
00:55:41,333 --> 00:55:43,208
[beeping]

1145
00:55:43,291 --> 00:55:45,166
Crow 7 to all units.

1146
00:55:45,250 --> 00:55:47,708
System infiltration
was successful.

1147
00:55:47,791 --> 00:55:50,125
[beeping]

1148
00:55:50,208 --> 00:55:52,291
[STIYL] We're going to
put an end to all this.

1149
00:55:52,375 --> 00:55:53,583
What are you saying?

1150
00:55:53,666 --> 00:55:55,333
The president,
Ladylee Tangleroad,

1151
00:55:55,416 --> 00:55:57,083
was originally
on our side.

1152
00:55:57,166 --> 00:55:59,625
She's a sybil, specializing
in Greek divination.

1153
00:55:59,708 --> 00:56:01,833
Unfortunately,
it seems she's gone rogue,

1154
00:56:01,916 --> 00:56:04,750
trying to construct a spell
with Arisa at its core.

1155
00:56:04,833 --> 00:56:06,166
She's using Endymion.

1156
00:56:06,250 --> 00:56:08,416
We're talking about
a colossal spell.

1157
00:56:08,500 --> 00:56:09,625
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Something
with enough power

1158
00:56:09,708 --> 00:56:11,708
to wipe out the entire
northern hemisphere

1159
00:56:11,791 --> 00:56:13,583
if we allow it
to be activated.

1160
00:56:13,666 --> 00:56:15,125
[gasps]

1161
00:56:15,208 --> 00:56:18,083
So, at any rate, as long as
the problem is a magical one,

1162
00:56:18,166 --> 00:56:20,000
it falls within
our territory.

1163
00:56:20,083 --> 00:56:22,083
Which means you guys
can keep out of it.

1164
00:56:22,166 --> 00:56:23,583
You sure you
can handle it?

1165
00:56:23,666 --> 00:56:25,166
I mean it is
outer space.

1166
00:56:25,250 --> 00:56:28,250
We can deal with the core.
And if it's necessary,

1167
00:56:28,333 --> 00:56:30,666
[STIYL] we'll destroy
the tower itself.

1168
00:56:30,750 --> 00:56:32,458
When you say you can
"deal with the core"

1169
00:56:32,541 --> 00:56:35,083
do you mean you're
going to kill Arisa?

1170
00:56:35,166 --> 00:56:37,291
Sorry, kid. There's no choice.

1171
00:56:38,291 --> 00:56:41,375
[KAMIJO] You don't
know her. She has a dream.

1172
00:56:41,458 --> 00:56:44,125
She's poured her entire
heart into pursuing it.

1173
00:56:45,166 --> 00:56:46,833
Why is she being
treated like the villain,

1174
00:56:46,916 --> 00:56:48,416
as if she's the one
responsible for some

1175
00:56:48,500 --> 00:56:51,000
[KAMIJO] crazy plan
to tear the world apart?

1176
00:56:51,833 --> 00:56:53,250
Uh.

1177
00:56:55,708 --> 00:56:56,958
Toma! Stop!

1178
00:56:57,041 --> 00:56:58,208
[INDEX] You shouldn't be up yet!

1179
00:56:58,291 --> 00:57:00,958
There's no choice;
we're running out of time.

1180
00:57:01,041 --> 00:57:02,791
[KAMIJO] Whether by
science or by magic,

1181
00:57:02,875 --> 00:57:04,333
Arisa is going to be killed.

1182
00:57:04,416 --> 00:57:05,791
Huh?

1183
00:57:07,250 --> 00:57:09,375
I see he's as
big a fool as ever.

1184
00:57:09,458 --> 00:57:10,958
[INDEX] I'm coming, too!

1185
00:57:11,041 --> 00:57:12,208
We had a feeling
you'd say that,

1186
00:57:12,291 --> 00:57:13,958
so we got something
ready for ya.

1187
00:57:14,041 --> 00:57:15,000
[KAMIJO] Huh?

1188
00:57:15,083 --> 00:57:16,541
[MISAKA SISTERS] "Stare."

1189
00:57:16,625 --> 00:57:18,583
[LAST ORDER] "Yes, yes.
I see what you mean.

1190
00:57:18,666 --> 00:57:22,000
It sounds like this could be a
real mess in the making, huh?"

1191
00:57:22,083 --> 00:57:25,375
agrees Misaka Misaka,
using her best stage whisper.

1192
00:57:25,458 --> 00:57:26,750
[laughing]

1193
00:57:26,833 --> 00:57:29,375
Quiet down, will ya?
Whispers aren't supposed to

1194
00:57:29,458 --> 00:57:33,125
be that loud,
you know. Dumb girl.

1195
00:57:33,208 --> 00:57:34,666
[giggles]

1196
00:57:36,375 --> 00:57:39,791
[MIKOTO] Hey, thirsty?
I raided the vending machine.

1197
00:57:39,875 --> 00:57:42,833
Where is he?
Why that little!

1198
00:57:46,041 --> 00:57:47,625
[LADYLEE] A plane
fell from outer space,

1199
00:57:47,708 --> 00:57:49,375
and eighty-eight
people survived.

1200
00:57:49,458 --> 00:57:51,791
If that isn't a miracle,
then what is it?

1201
00:57:52,875 --> 00:57:55,208
[door opens]

1202
00:57:55,291 --> 00:57:56,916
[CROW 7] Sorry for the delay.

1203
00:57:58,333 --> 00:57:59,291
What's our status?

1204
00:57:59,375 --> 00:58:01,291
Ladylee's
headed into space.

1205
00:58:01,375 --> 00:58:03,541
The operation's
advanced to Phase 4.

1206
00:58:03,625 --> 00:58:05,291
[CROW 7] An Antiskill
squad is approaching

1207
00:58:05,375 --> 00:58:06,750
Endymion as we speak.

1208
00:58:06,833 --> 00:58:08,083
So are we ready to go up?

1209
00:58:08,166 --> 00:58:09,541
Yes, we're ready.

1210
00:58:12,666 --> 00:58:13,833
Are you sure, ma'am?

1211
00:58:13,916 --> 00:58:16,041
This is something I
need to settle myself.

1212
00:58:16,125 --> 00:58:18,958
Don't send anybody
else up after me.

1213
00:58:19,041 --> 00:58:20,416
[SHUTAURA] I'm off.

1214
00:58:28,583 --> 00:58:34,541
[CROWD commotion]

1215
00:58:34,625 --> 00:58:36,291
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER B] Attention:
we are now temporarily

1216
00:58:36,375 --> 00:58:37,875
shutting down the
network to adjust

1217
00:58:37,958 --> 00:58:40,000
the relay circuits
for the ceremony.

1218
00:58:40,083 --> 00:58:42,500
Please wait a moment
for service to resume.

1219
00:58:49,166 --> 00:58:50,500
[ARISA] A miracle.

1220
00:58:50,583 --> 00:58:52,750
I have a very special
request to make of you.

1221
00:58:52,833 --> 00:58:55,416
I'd like for you to
sing your miracle song.

1222
00:58:58,125 --> 00:59:00,416
[ARISA] I'm sorry, Toma.

1223
00:59:02,958 --> 00:59:05,208
What an ungrateful
wretch you are.

1224
00:59:08,833 --> 00:59:10,041
[LADYLEE] If it weren't
for me, you would still be

1225
00:59:10,125 --> 00:59:11,583
squawking on the sidewalks.

1226
00:59:11,666 --> 00:59:14,000
I gave you a real
stage to perform upon.

1227
00:59:14,083 --> 00:59:16,458
You can always refuse
my request if you like.

1228
00:59:16,541 --> 00:59:18,333
Of course, the
unfortunate result of your

1229
00:59:18,416 --> 00:59:21,916
refusal would be the deaths of
everybody who came here today.

1230
00:59:25,291 --> 00:59:27,666
[ARISA] Okay. I'll sing.
But that doesn't mean you win.

1231
00:59:27,750 --> 00:59:29,416
I won't be singing to
make either your dream

1232
00:59:29,500 --> 00:59:31,500
or mine come true.

1233
00:59:31,583 --> 00:59:33,166
[ARISA] My song will be
dedicated to the people

1234
00:59:33,250 --> 00:59:35,666
who are genuinely
looking forward to it.

1235
00:59:37,166 --> 00:59:38,750
[ARISA] It's them
I'll be singing for.

1236
00:59:38,833 --> 00:59:42,791
No matter what you plan, the
miracle song will rise above it.

1237
00:59:42,875 --> 00:59:46,833
It's stronger than
you are. A lot stronger.

1238
00:59:46,916 --> 00:59:51,291
[aircraft noise]

1239
00:59:51,375 --> 00:59:52,916
What is this?

1240
00:59:53,000 --> 00:59:55,625
It's a Ballistic Slider.
It has the dubious honor

1241
00:59:55,708 --> 00:59:57,541
[TSUCHIMIKADO] of being the
shuttle system that lost out

1242
00:59:57,625 --> 01:00:01,458
as the city's next big
space transport craft.

1243
01:00:01,541 --> 01:00:04,041
This baby's gonna take you
all the way to outer space!

1244
01:00:04,125 --> 01:00:05,791
What? It's going where?

1245
01:00:05,875 --> 01:00:08,708
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Outer space!
Keep up now, Kami.

1246
01:00:09,458 --> 01:00:11,291
[YOMIKAWA] What's the status of
the various underground tunnels

1247
01:00:11,375 --> 01:00:12,875
and payload routes?

1248
01:00:12,958 --> 01:00:14,833
All those paths
have been sealed off.

1249
01:00:14,916 --> 01:00:16,750
You know what that
means, don't you?

1250
01:00:16,833 --> 01:00:18,458
[YOMIKAWA] This bridge
is the only entry point

1251
01:00:18,541 --> 01:00:20,208
left open to us.

1252
01:00:21,541 --> 01:00:25,166
[cheering]

1253
01:00:25,250 --> 01:00:28,708
[ARISA] ♪ The stars shining
brightly and so beautifully ♪

1254
01:00:28,791 --> 01:00:32,250
♪ that put my mind at ease ♪

1255
01:00:34,416 --> 01:00:38,041
♪ Give me hope ♪

1256
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:41,791
Alright, boys, let's go!

1257
01:00:42,291 --> 01:00:51,291
♪

1258
01:00:51,375 --> 01:00:52,916
♪ Many sleepless nights, ♪

1259
01:00:53,000 --> 01:00:57,041
♪ I'd search for
comfort up above me ♪

1260
01:00:57,125 --> 01:01:02,875
♪ I believed that the stars
were always listening ♪

1261
01:01:02,958 --> 01:01:05,041
[ARISA] ♪ But my fear
overcame the faith ♪

1262
01:01:05,125 --> 01:01:07,333
♪ that I once
had in happiness ♪

1263
01:01:07,416 --> 01:01:09,166
It's all up to you
now, man. Go get 'em.

1264
01:01:09,250 --> 01:01:12,458
[ARISA] ♪ The glow of my tears
that trickled down my cheeks ♪

1265
01:01:12,541 --> 01:01:13,875
♪ are what became ♪

1266
01:01:13,958 --> 01:01:17,166
--That's our cue. Let's go.
--♪ My shooting star ♪

1267
01:01:17,250 --> 01:01:18,583
--Yeah!
--♪ My shooting star ♪

1268
01:01:18,666 --> 01:01:20,333
--[MARYE and MARYBETH] Yeah!
--♪ My shooting star ♪

1269
01:01:20,416 --> 01:01:23,916
♪ And I flick them away like
they were grains of sand ♪

1270
01:01:24,000 --> 01:01:26,208
♪ (The stars
twinkle in the sky) ♪

1271
01:01:26,291 --> 01:01:27,333
♪ But I'm not giving up hope ♪

1272
01:01:27,416 --> 01:01:29,583
♪ that one day I could see ♪

1273
01:01:29,666 --> 01:01:33,875
♪ A great light, make a wish, ♪

1274
01:01:33,958 --> 01:01:36,541
♪ that will finally
reach to the sky ♪

1275
01:01:36,625 --> 01:01:39,250
♪ If I let emotions
run so high ♪

1276
01:01:39,333 --> 01:01:43,125
♪ they stretch to meet
the heavens above ♪

1277
01:01:43,208 --> 01:01:46,791
♪ Know that my intention's
always been to wish ♪

1278
01:01:46,875 --> 01:01:48,375
♪ your happiness ♪

1279
01:01:48,458 --> 01:01:50,500
--♪ I'm one step away from... ♪
--[LADYLEE] Life and death.

1280
01:01:50,583 --> 01:01:52,416
Finite and infinite.

1281
01:01:52,500 --> 01:01:54,916
So many contrasting
concepts intersecting.

1282
01:01:55,000 --> 01:01:56,416
There are different
laws in space than

1283
01:01:56,500 --> 01:01:57,958
there are on the ground.

1284
01:01:58,041 --> 01:02:00,083
[LADYLEE] The fanaticism and
blood of the people will be

1285
01:02:00,166 --> 01:02:03,083
an offering given in a
feast to appease the gods.

1286
01:02:03,166 --> 01:02:04,708
Their life's breath is key!

1287
01:02:04,791 --> 01:02:08,375
When they all die, Endymion's
curse will be broken!

1288
01:02:08,458 --> 01:02:09,916
[ARISA'S song] ♪ Tonight
I'll make it come true ♪

1289
01:02:10,000 --> 01:02:10,791
[gasps]

1290
01:02:10,875 --> 01:02:12,500
Wow, look up there!

1291
01:02:12,583 --> 01:02:14,500
[INDEX] Amazing! I've
never seen a magic array

1292
01:02:14,583 --> 01:02:16,083
as big as this one!

1293
01:02:16,166 --> 01:02:19,416
It actually brings in the Earth
itself as part of the spell.

1294
01:02:19,500 --> 01:02:21,333
[KAMIJO] What happens
once it's activated?

1295
01:02:21,416 --> 01:02:24,541
I really can't say without
knowing what its objective is.

1296
01:02:24,625 --> 01:02:26,666
I do think it's
Goetian in nature,

1297
01:02:26,750 --> 01:02:28,583
[INDEX] but this isn't
in any of the records.

1298
01:02:28,666 --> 01:02:30,166
[beeping]

1299
01:02:30,250 --> 01:02:32,291
Uh, that sounds bad!

1300
01:02:32,375 --> 01:02:34,541
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Hey,
travelers! How's it goin'?

1301
01:02:34,625 --> 01:02:36,208
Forgive the intrusion,
but I've got some

1302
01:02:36,291 --> 01:02:38,708
unfortunate news, uh...

1303
01:02:38,791 --> 01:02:41,041
The elevator's equipped
with anti-debris missiles,

1304
01:02:41,125 --> 01:02:42,791
and it seems
they're locked on you.

1305
01:02:42,875 --> 01:02:45,500
[KAMIJO] What're we supposed
to do? Do we have any weapons?

1306
01:02:45,583 --> 01:02:47,041
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Are you
kidding? Of course!

1307
01:02:47,125 --> 01:02:49,416
[ARISA'S song] ♪ ...Polaris,
shining over me ♪

1308
01:02:49,500 --> 01:02:52,333
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Okay!
Looks like you're up!

1309
01:02:52,416 --> 01:02:56,416
Tsuchimikado.
I won't forget about this.

1310
01:02:57,125 --> 01:02:58,458
[KANZAKI grunts]

1311
01:02:58,541 --> 01:03:00,625
[ARISA'S song] ♪ If I let
emotions run so high ♪

1312
01:03:00,708 --> 01:03:04,666
♪ they stretch to meet
the heavens above ♪

1313
01:03:04,750 --> 01:03:08,083
♪ Know that my intention's
always been to wish ♪

1314
01:03:08,166 --> 01:03:09,708
♪ our happiness ♪

1315
01:03:09,791 --> 01:03:14,416
♪ The sky is exactly like our
dreams because to both of them ♪

1316
01:03:14,500 --> 01:03:16,083
♪ there is no end ♪

1317
01:03:16,166 --> 01:03:22,000
♪ So I let my voice ring out
and sing as loud as I can ♪

1318
01:03:22,083 --> 01:03:23,875
♪ I want to make
sure my emotions ♪

1319
01:03:23,958 --> 01:03:28,291
♪ find their way back to you. ♪

1320
01:03:28,375 --> 01:03:29,666
--[yells]
--♪ For ages to come ♪

1321
01:03:29,750 --> 01:03:33,208
--♪ For ages to come ♪

1322
01:03:37,041 --> 01:03:38,291
[ARISA'S song] ♪ A star
in the whole sky, ♪

1323
01:03:38,375 --> 01:03:39,666
♪ Tonight I'll
make it come true ♪

1324
01:03:39,750 --> 01:03:42,708
[KANZAKI] Well, Toma Kamijo,
the rest is up to you.

1325
01:03:42,791 --> 01:03:44,125
[ARISA'S song] ♪ Your
smile is so dazzling ♪

1326
01:03:44,208 --> 01:03:45,541
♪ Let's make a chain spiraling ♪

1327
01:03:45,625 --> 01:03:48,500
♪ Through joining
hands we will be ♪

1328
01:03:48,583 --> 01:03:49,916
♪ A star in the whole sky ♪

1329
01:03:50,000 --> 01:03:51,375
♪ Tonight I'll make
it to come true ♪

1330
01:03:51,458 --> 01:03:54,333
♪ Oh please,
just let it come true ♪

1331
01:03:54,416 --> 01:03:57,208
♪ Our smiles are so dazzling
Links of our imagining ♪

1332
01:03:57,291 --> 01:04:01,166
♪ Create a future of light ♪

1333
01:04:03,375 --> 01:04:07,666
[CROWD cheering]

1334
01:04:12,750 --> 01:04:22,708
[beeping]

1335
01:04:32,416 --> 01:04:33,375
Where's our backup?

1336
01:04:33,458 --> 01:04:36,583
They say it'll
still be awhile.

1337
01:04:36,666 --> 01:04:38,041
Huh?

1338
01:04:41,250 --> 01:04:42,625
[MIKOTO grunts]

1339
01:04:43,458 --> 01:04:45,541
That dirty sneak!
Does he really think

1340
01:04:45,625 --> 01:04:47,791
he can leave me behind?

1341
01:04:47,875 --> 01:04:50,166
[MIKOTO] You'd think he would
know better than that by now.

1342
01:04:50,250 --> 01:04:52,083
Next time he won't forget!

1343
01:04:59,750 --> 01:05:01,541
Listen, you think
you can do me a favor?

1344
01:05:01,625 --> 01:05:02,625
Huh?

1345
01:05:02,708 --> 01:05:04,375
Stay here and keep
an eye on things.

1346
01:05:04,458 --> 01:05:05,833
You're going in
there without me?

1347
01:05:05,916 --> 01:05:09,166
You're the only person
I can ask. Please do it.

1348
01:05:09,250 --> 01:05:10,166
Hmm.

1349
01:05:11,625 --> 01:05:12,750
Good luck, Sissy!

1350
01:05:12,833 --> 01:05:14,125
[MIKOTO] I'm counting on you!

1351
01:05:14,208 --> 01:05:15,541
Be careful!

1352
01:05:15,625 --> 01:05:17,083
[whimpers]

1353
01:05:17,166 --> 01:05:19,875
♪

1354
01:05:19,958 --> 01:05:21,083
[STIYL] We're moving in.

1355
01:05:21,166 --> 01:05:22,083
--[MARYE] Right!
--[MARYBETH] Right, Master!

1356
01:05:22,166 --> 01:05:23,541
[JANE] Yes, sir!

1357
01:05:28,333 --> 01:05:31,833
Goodness. It looks like
quite a commotion down there.

1358
01:05:31,916 --> 01:05:33,750
It makes no difference;
they're all too late.

1359
01:05:33,833 --> 01:05:35,041
[SHUTAURA]
Are you sure about that?

1360
01:05:35,125 --> 01:05:36,500
[gun cocks]

1361
01:05:36,583 --> 01:05:41,416
♪

1362
01:05:48,541 --> 01:05:51,666
[LADYLEE] Silly girl. I
didn't think you would come.

1363
01:05:51,750 --> 01:05:53,166
[gunshot]

1364
01:05:58,541 --> 01:06:00,291
[LADYLEE retches]

1365
01:06:01,958 --> 01:06:03,791
I said I would stop you.

1366
01:06:03,875 --> 01:06:05,833
I intend to keep that promise.

1367
01:06:05,916 --> 01:06:08,375
[gunfire]

1368
01:06:12,666 --> 01:06:22,833
♪

1369
01:06:22,916 --> 01:06:25,166
[coughs]

1370
01:06:27,000 --> 01:06:33,041
[LADYLEE] I... I'm more than a
thousand years old, you know.

1371
01:06:33,125 --> 01:06:36,750
I was upset when the
Orion experiment failed.

1372
01:06:36,833 --> 01:06:39,500
But it was alright because
something unexpected

1373
01:06:39,583 --> 01:06:43,541
came out of it.
That something was Arisa.

1374
01:06:43,625 --> 01:06:45,625
[LADYLEE]
Her power is miraculous.

1375
01:06:45,708 --> 01:06:48,375
With it, I will be able to die.

1376
01:06:48,458 --> 01:06:50,875
What do you say?
Shall we end this together?

1377
01:06:54,208 --> 01:06:55,458
I don't think so!

1378
01:06:55,541 --> 01:06:56,916
[running footsteps]

1379
01:06:58,416 --> 01:07:08,375
♪

1380
01:07:17,666 --> 01:07:20,291
[grunting]

1381
01:07:21,458 --> 01:07:23,583
[SHUTAURA struggling]

1382
01:07:23,666 --> 01:07:26,375
[alarm beeping]

1383
01:07:26,458 --> 01:07:28,333
What's happening now?

1384
01:07:28,416 --> 01:07:32,916
[alarm beeping]

1385
01:07:34,541 --> 01:07:36,666
[MIKOTO] Whoa! What that
was that? What happened?

1386
01:07:36,750 --> 01:07:38,958
Let's see. It isn't good.
It looks like there was

1387
01:07:39,041 --> 01:07:42,458
some kind of an explosion near
the elevator relay station.

1388
01:07:42,541 --> 01:07:44,416
[UIHARU] And, as a result,
the stress balances

1389
01:07:44,500 --> 01:07:46,250
are starting to come undone!

1390
01:07:46,333 --> 01:07:48,041
Wait, so,
are you saying?

1391
01:07:48,125 --> 01:07:49,416
[UIHARU]
If something isn't done,

1392
01:07:49,500 --> 01:07:51,458
the elevator is
going to collapse.

1393
01:07:51,541 --> 01:07:53,708
It will plummet
back down to Earth!

1394
01:08:03,916 --> 01:08:06,833
[CROWD commotion]

1395
01:08:06,916 --> 01:08:09,166
[MAN D] That sounded like
a freakin' huge explosion.

1396
01:08:09,250 --> 01:08:10,625
--[MAN E] No way.
--[WOMAN B] I'm scared!

1397
01:08:10,708 --> 01:08:12,375
[MAN G] Oh, man
we're in outer space!

1398
01:08:12,458 --> 01:08:13,916
[WOMAN C] What's
going to happen now?

1399
01:08:14,500 --> 01:08:16,291
[CROWD gasps and screams]

1400
01:08:16,375 --> 01:08:18,041
[WOMAN D]
Whoa, are you all right?

1401
01:08:18,125 --> 01:08:19,541
[MAN H] We're gonna die!

1402
01:08:19,625 --> 01:08:25,916
[CROWD commmotion]

1403
01:08:30,625 --> 01:08:35,791
[ARISA] Wait. What did
I do the last time?

1404
01:08:35,875 --> 01:08:37,750
Who's in charge?
Do something!

1405
01:08:37,833 --> 01:08:39,750
Get us out of
here already!

1406
01:08:39,833 --> 01:08:45,333
[ARISA] ♪ Wondering as I
look up to the stars above ♪

1407
01:08:45,416 --> 01:08:50,458
♪ If the sun will shine
tomorrow like it always does? ♪

1408
01:08:50,541 --> 01:08:56,166
♪ You and I go walking on,
under starlight so luminous ♪

1409
01:08:56,250 --> 01:08:57,625
--♪ "They look close ♪

1410
01:08:57,708 --> 01:08:59,000
--[FEMALE STUDENT A] A song?
--♪ enough to touch," ♪

1411
01:08:59,083 --> 01:09:00,416
♪ so we say ♪

1412
01:09:00,500 --> 01:09:06,291
♪ As we laugh
and stroll along ♪

1413
01:09:06,375 --> 01:09:19,958
♪

1414
01:09:20,041 --> 01:09:23,333
Okay, if you folks
will follow me, please?

1415
01:09:23,416 --> 01:09:24,958
♪ ...I thought of you ♪

1416
01:09:25,041 --> 01:09:27,583
♪ Reaching out to you ♪

1417
01:09:27,666 --> 01:09:31,041
♪ I text...
what I'm feeling ♪

1418
01:09:31,125 --> 01:09:33,875
♪ Anxiety buries me ♪

1419
01:09:33,958 --> 01:09:35,208
♪ Beneath my hopes... ♪

1420
01:09:35,291 --> 01:09:37,500
[LADYLEE] That's the...
thirty-eighth explosion...

1421
01:09:37,583 --> 01:09:39,000
I've been in...

1422
01:09:39,083 --> 01:09:41,041
It is the first time
I've ever been exposed

1423
01:09:41,125 --> 01:09:43,458
to a vacuum, though.

1424
01:09:43,541 --> 01:09:45,708
[LADYLEE]
This is it. I can tell.

1425
01:09:45,791 --> 01:09:48,541
Today is the day
I'm going to die!

1426
01:09:55,666 --> 01:09:57,500
What? Endymion is
going to collapse?

1427
01:09:57,583 --> 01:09:59,541
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Yeah.
Apparently, that's unavoidable

1428
01:09:59,625 --> 01:10:02,500
at this point. We're doing
everything we can on our end,

1429
01:10:02,583 --> 01:10:03,875
but I just don't
think it's gonna--

1430
01:10:03,958 --> 01:10:05,083
[static interception]

1431
01:10:05,166 --> 01:10:06,666
Hey! Hello? You there?

1432
01:10:06,750 --> 01:10:08,208
What do we do?

1433
01:10:10,000 --> 01:10:11,250
[KAMIJO] We need to split up.

1434
01:10:11,333 --> 01:10:12,541
Huh?

1435
01:10:12,625 --> 01:10:13,833
It's the only way.

1436
01:10:13,916 --> 01:10:15,583
You keep the magic
from activating.

1437
01:10:15,666 --> 01:10:19,416
Meanwhile, I'll go after Arisa.

1438
01:10:19,500 --> 01:10:21,125
You're right.
We should split up.

1439
01:10:21,208 --> 01:10:23,625
But you had better save
her! You hear me, Toma?

1440
01:10:23,708 --> 01:10:25,500
She and I made a
promise to each other.

1441
01:10:25,583 --> 01:10:27,000
We promised once
her song was done

1442
01:10:27,083 --> 01:10:29,500
[INDEX] we would
sing it together.

1443
01:10:29,583 --> 01:10:30,875
I'll bring her back.

1444
01:10:30,958 --> 01:10:32,791
[ARISA'S song] ♪ If the
sun will shine tomorrow ♪

1445
01:10:32,875 --> 01:10:34,291
♪ like it always does? ♪

1446
01:10:34,375 --> 01:10:36,541
[UIHARU] It's no use!
There's nothing we can do

1447
01:10:36,625 --> 01:10:38,291
to prevent it from collapsing!

1448
01:10:38,375 --> 01:10:39,875
Just calm down and think.

1449
01:10:39,958 --> 01:10:41,750
[MIKOTO] There must be
something left to try.

1450
01:10:41,833 --> 01:10:43,208
Let me see.

1451
01:10:45,166 --> 01:10:47,416
[UIHARU] There is an
emergency purge system.

1452
01:10:47,500 --> 01:10:50,708
Under normal circumstances,
it would be set off remotely.

1453
01:10:50,791 --> 01:10:52,500
And with everything
that's going on right now,

1454
01:10:52,583 --> 01:10:54,291
the system
itself is frozen.

1455
01:10:54,375 --> 01:10:56,458
Is there a way to
get it working again?

1456
01:10:56,541 --> 01:10:58,583
[UIHARU] If we can manually
set off all the blast bolts

1457
01:10:58,666 --> 01:11:00,583
in these three spots,
then maybe.

1458
01:11:00,666 --> 01:11:03,083
It's a long shot,
but it could work.

1459
01:11:04,333 --> 01:11:07,583
[MIKOTO] Right now, we should
try anything we can.

1460
01:11:07,666 --> 01:11:09,708
I'll take one
of the locations.

1461
01:11:09,791 --> 01:11:13,041
I'll help you, Sissy. I'm
on my way there right now!

1462
01:11:13,125 --> 01:11:14,000
[groans]

1463
01:11:14,083 --> 01:11:15,666
But, you're in no shape!

1464
01:11:15,750 --> 01:11:17,375
I'll take the second location.

1465
01:11:17,458 --> 01:11:19,041
But we still
need someone else.

1466
01:11:19,125 --> 01:11:21,541
Alright, folks, we've only
got one more strike to go!

1467
01:11:21,625 --> 01:11:23,041
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
Hello, ladies and gents!

1468
01:11:23,125 --> 01:11:25,166
Long time listener,
first time caller here!

1469
01:11:25,250 --> 01:11:26,916
It's a real pleasure
to be speaking with

1470
01:11:27,000 --> 01:11:29,375
all of you fine people!

1471
01:11:29,458 --> 01:11:31,416
I heard about your situation.

1472
01:11:31,500 --> 01:11:32,791
If you'll leave it
to me, I've got a way

1473
01:11:32,875 --> 01:11:35,083
[TSUCHIMIKADO] to deal
with the third blast bolt.

1474
01:11:35,166 --> 01:11:36,375
Who is that?

1475
01:11:36,458 --> 01:11:37,708
[ANTISKILL C] No idea.

1476
01:11:37,791 --> 01:11:39,125
I don't know who that is,
but if he can break in

1477
01:11:39,208 --> 01:11:41,375
on an Antiskill encrypted
line, chances are he's not

1478
01:11:41,458 --> 01:11:43,541
just some prankster.
We're out of time!

1479
01:11:43,625 --> 01:11:45,666
[MIKOTO] I say we let
the mystery man help.

1480
01:11:46,208 --> 01:11:50,166
[TSUCHIMIKADO] You get all that,
Stiyl? It's up to you, now.

1481
01:11:50,250 --> 01:11:53,375
Yeah, I got it.
I am at your service.

1482
01:11:53,458 --> 01:11:54,500
[SHUTAURA groans]

1483
01:11:54,583 --> 01:11:58,375
Make the noise stop!
Must make it stop!

1484
01:11:58,958 --> 01:12:02,666
Screeching like this
can work a miracle?

1485
01:12:02,750 --> 01:12:05,875
[SHUTAURA]
I will stop it. I swear!

1486
01:12:05,958 --> 01:12:11,000
[ARISA] ♪ If the sun will shine
tomorrow like it always does? ♪

1487
01:12:11,083 --> 01:12:14,000
♪ If you wish it hard enough ♪

1488
01:12:14,083 --> 01:12:16,833
♪ It's sure to
come true someday ♪

1489
01:12:16,916 --> 01:12:22,083
[ARISA] ♪ Just
believe in yourself ♪

1490
01:12:22,166 --> 01:12:24,541
--[SHUTAURA] No.
--♪ Wondering as I look up ♪

1491
01:12:24,625 --> 01:12:28,041
--[SHUTAURA] Stop it!
--♪ to the stars above ♪

1492
01:12:29,541 --> 01:12:30,875
[screams]

1493
01:12:30,958 --> 01:12:33,000
[KAMIJO panting]

1494
01:12:33,083 --> 01:12:34,750
[KAMIJO grunts]
[ARISA yelps]

1495
01:12:37,458 --> 01:12:38,833
[grunts]

1496
01:12:47,958 --> 01:12:49,916
Uh, where did
you come from?

1497
01:12:51,041 --> 01:12:53,000
Never mind that. I'm--

1498
01:12:53,083 --> 01:12:54,541
[grunts]

1499
01:12:56,875 --> 01:12:57,708
[gasps]

1500
01:12:57,791 --> 01:12:59,416
What's happening, Toma?

1501
01:12:59,500 --> 01:13:04,000
♪

1502
01:13:04,083 --> 01:13:06,708
Almost there.
A little farther.

1503
01:13:06,791 --> 01:13:08,791
[LADYLEE] It won't be long now.

1504
01:13:12,041 --> 01:13:15,666
[INDEX] I admit, I've never seen
a spell as crazy as this one.

1505
01:13:15,750 --> 01:13:18,041
Are you trying to
destroy the planet?

1506
01:13:18,125 --> 01:13:19,750
All the lines you've
used to refine your

1507
01:13:19,833 --> 01:13:23,166
magical power are skewed
way beyond what's rational.

1508
01:13:23,250 --> 01:13:25,291
You're the List
of Prohibited Books.

1509
01:13:25,375 --> 01:13:28,208
Yes, I've heard of you.
A human library.

1510
01:13:28,291 --> 01:13:32,333
[LADYLEE] A vessel for 103,000
volumes of magical grimoires.

1511
01:13:32,416 --> 01:13:34,500
I would think that
you would understand.

1512
01:13:34,583 --> 01:13:36,375
Surely you of all
people know what it's like

1513
01:13:36,458 --> 01:13:37,958
to be cursed by magic.

1514
01:13:38,041 --> 01:13:40,041
[LADYLEE] I want to
escape this living hell.

1515
01:13:40,125 --> 01:13:42,625
Please, won't you let me?

1516
01:13:42,708 --> 01:13:45,333
[INDEX] It won't work. Even
if this crazy plan succeeds,

1517
01:13:45,416 --> 01:13:48,208
you won't die. I can
tell you that much.

1518
01:13:48,291 --> 01:13:49,166
Uh!

1519
01:13:49,250 --> 01:13:51,000
Okay, here we go!

1520
01:13:52,791 --> 01:13:57,041
♪

1521
01:13:57,125 --> 01:13:58,625
Damn! If we don't hurry up,

1522
01:13:58,708 --> 01:14:00,875
it'll be too late
to do any good.

1523
01:14:08,083 --> 01:14:09,458
[MARYBETH] Uh!

1524
01:14:12,083 --> 01:14:13,333
[STIYL] Be more careful!

1525
01:14:13,416 --> 01:14:14,541
[MARYBETH] Sorry, Master!

1526
01:14:14,625 --> 01:14:16,208
Here they come!

1527
01:14:16,291 --> 01:14:18,583
[KAMIJO struggling]

1528
01:14:18,666 --> 01:14:20,125
What's the matter?

1529
01:14:20,208 --> 01:14:24,291
[footsteps]

1530
01:14:24,375 --> 01:14:25,750
[gun cocks]

1531
01:14:31,625 --> 01:14:33,833
[KAMIJO] Shutaura,
you don't need to do this!

1532
01:14:33,916 --> 01:14:35,166
[SHUTAURA]
This is all her fault.

1533
01:14:35,250 --> 01:14:39,041
Her existence is what
inspired Ladylee's plan...

1534
01:14:39,125 --> 01:14:41,166
and led to the unknown death.

1535
01:14:41,250 --> 01:14:44,083
Her stupid songs. The
supposed miracles they work

1536
01:14:44,166 --> 01:14:45,875
are nothing but illusions!

1537
01:14:45,958 --> 01:14:48,583
That's why she needs to die!

1538
01:14:51,041 --> 01:14:53,500
[SHUTAURA] How dare you?
This is no joke!

1539
01:14:53,583 --> 01:14:55,291
Ahhh!

1540
01:14:56,708 --> 01:14:58,791
[UIHARU] Okay, Misaka,
after your next right,

1541
01:14:58,875 --> 01:15:00,208
you should reach the target.

1542
01:15:00,291 --> 01:15:01,666
Got it, thanks!

1543
01:15:02,666 --> 01:15:04,041
[gasps]

1544
01:15:07,500 --> 01:15:10,125
[UIHARU] What is it, Misaka?
Is something wrong?

1545
01:15:10,208 --> 01:15:10,833
Are you okay?

1546
01:15:10,916 --> 01:15:11,958
Does it hurt badly?

1547
01:15:12,041 --> 01:15:13,375
Master.

1548
01:15:13,458 --> 01:15:16,333
Don't worry about me.
This is nothing but a scratch.

1549
01:15:16,416 --> 01:15:17,791
[MARYBETH and MARYE gasp]

1550
01:15:21,166 --> 01:15:23,708
Master. Allow us to
take care of this.

1551
01:15:23,791 --> 01:15:25,416
Now you're being ridiculous.

1552
01:15:25,500 --> 01:15:26,875
I told you, I'm fine.

1553
01:15:26,958 --> 01:15:29,250
I'm going to see this thing
through to the bitter end.

1554
01:15:30,458 --> 01:15:33,500
Yomikawa reporting in.
We're pinned down.

1555
01:15:33,583 --> 01:15:36,125
[YOMIKAWA] It doesn't look like
I'm going to get there in time.

1556
01:15:37,208 --> 01:15:38,583
[MISAKA 10032]
"That's acceptable."

1557
01:15:39,666 --> 01:15:41,208
[MISAKA 10032] "Please
proceed as planned and detonate

1558
01:15:41,291 --> 01:15:43,333
on the three-count as
previously determined,"

1559
01:15:43,416 --> 01:15:44,916
requests Misaka politely.

1560
01:15:45,000 --> 01:15:46,708
[KUROKO]
That sounded like Sissy.

1561
01:15:58,125 --> 01:15:59,583
[ACCELERATOR] Oh, come on.

1562
01:15:59,666 --> 01:16:02,166
Dragging me out of bed
for this? I was resting.

1563
01:16:02,250 --> 01:16:03,833
[ACCELERATOR] Why couldn't
they have left me in peace?

1564
01:16:03,916 --> 01:16:06,208
"Isn't it obvious?
If Endymion fell down,

1565
01:16:06,291 --> 01:16:07,458
[LAST ORDER] it would
mess up the whole planet,

1566
01:16:07,541 --> 01:16:09,000
and nobody would
have anywhere to live.

1567
01:16:09,083 --> 01:16:11,291
You wouldn't even have a
bed to get your rest in,"

1568
01:16:11,375 --> 01:16:13,291
says Misaka Misaka,
pointing out what must be

1569
01:16:13,375 --> 01:16:15,000
the most apparent reason.

1570
01:16:16,208 --> 01:16:18,708
Oh. Saving the Earth, huh?

1571
01:16:18,791 --> 01:16:22,041
Can't say I care about that,
but since I'm here anyway.

1572
01:16:22,125 --> 01:16:24,958
[ACCELERATOR] At least this'll
be good physical therapy.

1573
01:16:25,041 --> 01:16:29,000
[MIKOTO] There's no time for
hesitation now. Let's do this!

1574
01:16:30,125 --> 01:16:31,500
Three!

1575
01:16:37,583 --> 01:16:39,333
Two!

1576
01:16:45,666 --> 01:16:47,333
[yells]

1577
01:16:50,791 --> 01:16:51,958
What's happening now?

1578
01:16:52,041 --> 01:16:52,916
Did they do it?

1579
01:16:53,000 --> 01:16:54,916
Take cover!

1580
01:16:56,250 --> 01:16:59,125
[glass shattering]

1581
01:16:59,208 --> 01:17:00,166
[gasps]

1582
01:17:00,250 --> 01:17:01,458
[LADYLEE] What is this?

1583
01:17:01,541 --> 01:17:04,750
Are they activating the
elevator's purge system?

1584
01:17:05,666 --> 01:17:08,500
[INDEX] Okay, this is my chance.
I need to unpack the layers

1585
01:17:08,583 --> 01:17:12,166
of her spell. There must
be some way to collapse it.

1586
01:17:14,375 --> 01:17:16,333
They detonated
Endymion's base?

1587
01:17:16,416 --> 01:17:18,791
They're doing whatever
needs to be done.

1588
01:17:18,875 --> 01:17:21,791
Whatever it takes to
get everyone out of this.

1589
01:17:23,875 --> 01:17:25,041
[sighs]

1590
01:17:25,125 --> 01:17:26,666
[gun cocks]

1591
01:17:26,750 --> 01:17:27,833
[SHUTAURA] You don't get it.

1592
01:17:27,916 --> 01:17:30,166
My father was the
pilot of the Orion.

1593
01:17:30,250 --> 01:17:33,416
He was also the sole
casualty of that accident.

1594
01:17:34,541 --> 01:17:38,125
[SHUTAURA] I survived,
and so did the others.

1595
01:17:38,208 --> 01:17:40,208
All eighty-eight of us!

1596
01:17:40,958 --> 01:17:44,250
That's why I stopped believing
in so-called "miracles."

1597
01:17:44,333 --> 01:17:46,333
My father
didn't get a miracle.

1598
01:17:46,416 --> 01:17:47,750
[SHUTAURA] He fought
with everything he had

1599
01:17:47,833 --> 01:17:51,625
to save that plane. What
good did it do? He's dead!

1600
01:17:53,541 --> 01:17:55,916
It sounds like your
dad was a real hero.

1601
01:17:56,000 --> 01:17:58,458
He fought to protect you and
everyone else on the plane.

1602
01:17:58,541 --> 01:18:00,458
The odds were against him,
but he didn't let that

1603
01:18:00,541 --> 01:18:02,458
stop him from trying, right?

1604
01:18:02,541 --> 01:18:04,166
He did what he needed to do.

1605
01:18:04,250 --> 01:18:06,458
He stepped up to the plate.

1606
01:18:06,541 --> 01:18:08,500
He hung in there, believing
he could make a difference,

1607
01:18:08,583 --> 01:18:10,291
right 'til the very end.

1608
01:18:10,375 --> 01:18:11,875
And how did that turn out?

1609
01:18:11,958 --> 01:18:15,000
His daughter and everybody else
who was on the Orion survived.

1610
01:18:15,083 --> 01:18:16,458
[gasps]

1611
01:18:18,708 --> 01:18:20,666
[KAMIJO] Something
special happened.

1612
01:18:20,750 --> 01:18:22,458
There was a miracle that day.

1613
01:18:22,541 --> 01:18:24,250
And your father was part of it.

1614
01:18:24,333 --> 01:18:26,958
You do him a great
disservice by denying it.

1615
01:18:27,041 --> 01:18:28,916
It's like you're killing
him all over again.

1616
01:18:29,000 --> 01:18:31,625
Is that any way to honor
the memory of a true hero?

1617
01:18:31,708 --> 01:18:33,083
[gasps]

1618
01:18:35,750 --> 01:18:38,875
[cell phone vibrates]

1619
01:18:38,958 --> 01:18:42,625
Come on. Answer, already.

1620
01:18:43,375 --> 01:18:44,916
[SHUTAURA] Damn.

1621
01:18:45,000 --> 01:18:46,500
Endymion really
is going to fall.

1622
01:18:46,583 --> 01:18:48,000
You weren't bluffing.

1623
01:18:48,083 --> 01:18:50,916
[laughing]

1624
01:18:51,000 --> 01:18:52,666
To hell with the
Miracle of the Eighty-Eight,

1625
01:18:52,750 --> 01:18:55,208
you hear me? And to hell
with miraculous songs!

1626
01:18:55,291 --> 01:18:58,000
Go on. I'd like to see how
you're going to save us now!

1627
01:18:58,083 --> 01:18:59,625
You're going to
keep Endymion from

1628
01:18:59,708 --> 01:19:01,166
crashing down to
Earth, are you?

1629
01:19:01,250 --> 01:19:03,541
You're going to save
everybody from certain death?

1630
01:19:03,625 --> 01:19:06,041
[SHUTAURA] You'll
save her. And yourself.

1631
01:19:06,125 --> 01:19:07,708
And every other
idiot who prefers

1632
01:19:07,791 --> 01:19:10,208
to believe in miracles
instead of reality!

1633
01:19:10,291 --> 01:19:11,541
[gasps]

1634
01:19:11,625 --> 01:19:12,833
[beep]

1635
01:19:12,916 --> 01:19:18,625
[ARISA'S melody]

1636
01:19:18,708 --> 01:19:20,666
[groans]

1637
01:19:20,750 --> 01:19:22,250
No! Stop!

1638
01:19:22,333 --> 01:19:23,708
[grunts]

1639
01:19:24,500 --> 01:19:25,791
[gasps]

1640
01:19:25,875 --> 01:19:27,250
Denying that
miracles can happen

1641
01:19:27,333 --> 01:19:30,000
doesn't help anything!
Belief is what saves people!

1642
01:19:30,083 --> 01:19:31,625
[grunts]

1643
01:19:33,916 --> 01:19:34,833
[KAMIJO] Ah!

1644
01:19:34,916 --> 01:19:37,833
[grunting]

1645
01:19:39,625 --> 01:19:42,458
[ARISA'S melody continues]

1646
01:19:42,541 --> 01:19:44,416
To get what you want in
life, you have to believe

1647
01:19:44,500 --> 01:19:45,916
you can do the impossible.

1648
01:19:46,000 --> 01:19:47,583
You have to pick a
dream and strive for it,

1649
01:19:47,666 --> 01:19:49,541
no matter what happens.

1650
01:19:49,625 --> 01:19:51,791
That's the only way you can
hope to make a difference.

1651
01:19:51,875 --> 01:19:53,916
To change the
world for the better!

1652
01:19:54,000 --> 01:19:56,166
[KAMIJO] Think about it!
That's what your father did

1653
01:19:56,250 --> 01:19:57,916
on the plane that day.

1654
01:19:58,000 --> 01:19:59,708
His belief that he
could do the impossible

1655
01:19:59,791 --> 01:20:00,958
was the true miracle!

1656
01:20:01,041 --> 01:20:01,916
[grunts]

1657
01:20:02,000 --> 01:20:03,250
You've got it wrong.

1658
01:20:03,333 --> 01:20:05,583
You're the one who
won't face reality.

1659
01:20:05,666 --> 01:20:08,291
So I'm going to
destroy your illusion!

1660
01:20:08,375 --> 01:20:10,333
[grunts]

1661
01:20:10,416 --> 01:20:12,208
[pained yell]

1662
01:20:13,500 --> 01:20:14,875
[SHUTAURA grunts]

1663
01:20:20,625 --> 01:20:22,583
[shaky exhale]

1664
01:20:27,375 --> 01:20:30,791
[KAMIJO] Hey,
you know, Shutaura,

1665
01:20:30,875 --> 01:20:33,208
music can be beautiful.

1666
01:20:33,291 --> 01:20:35,541
It really can.

1667
01:20:37,375 --> 01:20:39,625
[thud]

1668
01:20:44,125 --> 01:20:45,500
[KAMIJO] Damn it.

1669
01:20:48,250 --> 01:20:52,250
[KAMIJO] Not yet.
It's not over yet.

1670
01:20:53,541 --> 01:20:56,875
[SHUTAURA singing
ARISA'S melody]

1671
01:20:56,958 --> 01:20:59,000
[KAMIJO exhales heavily]

1672
01:20:59,083 --> 01:21:10,291
[SHUTAURA singing
ARISA'A melody]

1673
01:21:10,375 --> 01:21:20,333
[singing continues]

1674
01:21:21,500 --> 01:21:26,875
[worried chatter]

1675
01:21:30,625 --> 01:21:31,875
[beeping]

1676
01:21:31,958 --> 01:21:33,041
[COPILOT] The left engine
block has fallen away!

1677
01:21:33,125 --> 01:21:35,041
We won't make it. It's over!

1678
01:21:35,125 --> 01:21:36,500
Don't you dare give up now.

1679
01:21:36,583 --> 01:21:39,750
There must be
something that we can do!

1680
01:21:39,833 --> 01:21:41,291
[COPILOT panicking]

1681
01:21:41,375 --> 01:21:42,375
[PILOT] Stay calm.

1682
01:21:42,458 --> 01:21:44,125
[COPILOT screams]

1683
01:21:44,208 --> 01:21:45,708
[PILOT] Hey!

1684
01:21:53,583 --> 01:21:55,291
[YOUNG SHUTAURA]
Please, I'm begging you.

1685
01:21:55,375 --> 01:21:57,916
I'll sacrifice everything
that's precious to me.

1686
01:21:58,000 --> 01:22:02,458
Just please.
Work a miracle for us!

1687
01:22:02,541 --> 01:22:04,333
[grunts]

1688
01:22:04,416 --> 01:22:05,791
[SHUTAURA] That's right.

1689
01:22:06,833 --> 01:22:11,000
[SHUTAURA] Before we crashed,
I made a desperate wish.

1690
01:22:11,083 --> 01:22:13,500
I asked for a
miracle to happen.

1691
01:22:13,583 --> 01:22:17,583
I offered a sacrifice.
And then...

1692
01:22:17,666 --> 01:22:19,791
[ARISA] And then I was born.

1693
01:22:20,125 --> 01:22:30,083
[ARISA singing melody]

1694
01:22:36,041 --> 01:22:40,125
[ARISA] ♪ A symphony... ♪

1695
01:22:40,208 --> 01:22:43,333
What is that? A song?

1696
01:22:43,416 --> 01:22:45,833
[LADYLEE]
Oh no! It has to stop!

1697
01:22:45,916 --> 01:22:48,500
It's going to ruin everything!

1698
01:22:48,583 --> 01:22:50,583
Please stop this!

1699
01:22:50,666 --> 01:22:52,458
If that song keeps going,

1700
01:22:52,541 --> 01:22:55,250
if that kind of
power is released,

1701
01:22:55,333 --> 01:22:58,791
it'll fall apart.
My dream will be over!

1702
01:22:58,875 --> 01:23:01,041
[LADYLEE]
Please, this isn't fair!

1703
01:23:02,291 --> 01:23:07,750
[ARISA and SHUTAURA] ♪ And now
I know that I can sing ♪

1704
01:23:07,833 --> 01:23:14,416
♪ I have the
power to illuminate ♪

1705
01:23:14,500 --> 01:23:22,208
♪ Allowing love to
find a way, back to us ♪

1706
01:23:22,291 --> 01:23:27,875
♪ Here in eternity
may it rest ♪

1707
01:23:27,958 --> 01:23:33,541
♪ And then I know
I'll sing to you ♪

1708
01:23:33,625 --> 01:23:36,000
[ARISA and SHUTAURA] ♪ There's
nothing more that I could ♪

1709
01:23:36,083 --> 01:23:37,666
♪ lose from this ♪

1710
01:23:37,750 --> 01:23:39,958
What's happening, sir?
What do we do now?

1711
01:23:40,041 --> 01:23:41,750
It's gonna fall down!

1712
01:23:41,833 --> 01:23:42,750
[STIYL grunts]

1713
01:23:42,833 --> 01:23:44,250
[JANE, MALYBETH,
and MARYE scream]

1714
01:23:45,458 --> 01:23:47,833
"Wow! We're flying
through the air!"

1715
01:23:47,916 --> 01:23:50,041
exclaims Misaka Misaka.

1716
01:23:50,125 --> 01:23:51,916
[ACCELERATOR] Tch.
This is a one-time thing.

1717
01:23:52,000 --> 01:23:53,833
You understand that, right?

1718
01:23:56,750 --> 01:24:01,875
[MIKOTO panting]

1719
01:24:01,958 --> 01:24:05,125
[ARISA and SHUTAURA]
♪ And over again ♪

1720
01:24:05,208 --> 01:24:06,500
♪ Into the skies... ♪

1721
01:24:06,583 --> 01:24:08,000
The captain's up there.

1722
01:24:08,083 --> 01:24:09,708
[BOTH gasp]

1723
01:24:09,791 --> 01:24:11,541
Hey, look.
There's been a change.

1724
01:24:11,625 --> 01:24:13,208
Endymion is moving away from

1725
01:24:13,291 --> 01:24:15,250
[UIHARU] its previous
course of descent.

